  m_text: "Effective Date: [Tarih]\n\n[\u015Eirket Ad\u0131] (\"we,\" \"us,\" or
    \"our\") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains
    how we collect, use, and disclose information when you use our game, [Oyun Ad\u0131]
    (the \"Game\").\n\n1. Information We Collect\na) Personal Information\nWe do
    not collect personally identifiable information such as your name, address, or
    email unless you voluntarily provide it (e.g., for customer support).\n\nb) Device
    and Usage Data\nWe automatically collect certain information when you use the
    Game, including:\n\nDevice type and operating system\n\nUnique device identifiers
    (e.g., Advertising ID)\n\nIP address and approximate location\n\nGameplay data
    and interactions\n\nCrash reports and performance data\n\nThis data helps us
    improve the Game and provide you with a better experience.\n\nc) Analytics\nWe
    use third-party analytics services (such as Google Analytics, Unity Analytics,
    or similar) to collect and analyze aggregated usage data. These services may
    collect information such as session length, user behavior, and other gameplay
    statistics. This data is anonymous and does not identify individual users.\n\n2.
    How We Use Your Information\nTo operate and improve the Game\n\nTo understand
    how users interact with the Game\n\nTo diagnose and fix technical issues\n\nTo
    prevent fraud and enforce our Terms of Service\n\nTo communicate with you when
    necessary\n\n3. Information Sharing and Disclosure\nWe do not sell your personal
    information. We may share aggregated or anonymized data with third parties for
    analysis or marketing purposes.\n\nWe may also disclose information when required
    by law or to protect our rights.\n\n4. Data Security\nWe implement reasonable
    technical and organizational measures to protect your data from unauthorized
    access or disclosure.\n\n5. Your Choices\nYou can control certain data collection
    by adjusting your device settings, such as limiting ad tracking or disabling
    analytics permissions.\n\n6. Children's Privacy\nThe Game is not intended for
    children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal data from
    children under 13.\n\n7. Changes to This Policy\nWe may update this Privacy Policy
    from time to time. Changes will be posted with an updated effective date.\n\n8.
    Contact Us\nIf you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact
    us at:"
